Purpose
This file runs one agent safely under operational policies.

Linear intent
1. Open `Lwt.Syntax` so asynchronous steps read in direct order.
2. Define `with_timeout` to race the real promise against a sleep-based timeout failure.
3. Define `measure_latency_ms` to convert elapsed wall-clock time into integer milliseconds.
4. Define `build_item` to package one agent result into the standard batch item structure.
5. Define `failure_item` to create a consistent error result when the agent cannot be found or fails.
6. In `run_agent`, first ask the registry for the requested agent module.
7. If the agent is missing, log an error and return a typed failure item instead of crashing the runtime.
8. If the agent exists, capture the start time so latency can be measured after execution.
9. Build a retry policy from the runtime configuration.
10. Log the fact that this agent is about to run and on what kind of payload.
11. Run the agent under the retry policy and under the timeout wrapper.
12. When the run succeeds, compute the measured latency and overwrite the metrics latency field with the real value.
13. Package the successful output, metrics, and notes into one batch item.
14. If any exception escapes, turn it into a logged error and a typed failure item.

